last_episode_to_air.name: Bad Blood
last_episode_to_air.overview: The Annual Fire Department Blood Drive goes from good to bad when the Firefighters are forced to team up for charity with the Local Cops.

name: Tacoma FD
overview: There's not a lot of fires to fight in one of the rainiest cities in America, leaving the crew at the Tacoma Fire Department tackling the less glamorous elements of the job. Light on blazes that need extinguishing, this squad keeps itself entertained with creative competitions, friendly first responder rivalries, and bizarre emergency calls.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: Season 2 finds the squad fighting fires at a haunted house, trapped in an elevator during the annual Firefighter’s Ball, and creating fire safety videos with the buffest group of firefighters in Tacoma.

seasons.name: Season 4
seasons.overview: With Eddie employed by Shondaland and Andy leaving for the carpeting business, there are some big changes in the newly rebuilt (and slightly off-kilter) Station 24. A new Andy joins the crew, a wide-eyed probie who becomes the target of some comic hazing.

episodes.name: On the Hot Seat
episodes.overview: Tacoma FD's newest chief, Terry McConky, is under scrutiny by the city council to get serious about his station's ratings. Meanwhile, Terry's crew puts his job in jeopardy by engaging in a ridiculous competition for a super sawft prize.

episodes.name: Cop Wars
episodes.overview: Andy and Ike’s misstep on a call to a Tacoma police officer’s house fans the flames of the FD’s long-standing feud with the PD. Chief tries to keep a lid on the dispute, but all goes awry as his crew wages a tit-for-tat war with the cops.

episodes.name: A New Hope
episodes.overview: The crew is assigned their first ever female firefighter, Lucy, sending the firehouse into a gender confused tailspin. When Chief puts the clamp on rookie hazing, the guys try to engage in their old traditions anyway only to find that Lucy is a force to be reckoned with.

episodes.name: Training Day
episodes.overview: The Tacoma FD's negligence during a firehouse school trip makes Councilwoman Price so angry that she orders the guys to complete a training recertification with an old nemesis who's just itching to fail them.

episodes.name: The B-Team
episodes.overview: Andy's big welcome from a different team of firefighters has him questioning his place within his own crew. Meanwhile, Eddie spars with a new top chef at the station to win the annual pancake cook-off!

episodes.name: Full Moon Fever
episodes.overview: FD braces for a night of insane full moon rescue calls. Plus, Eddie and Granny go on active appendage duty and Ike gets bitten into an altered state.

episodes.name: Old Flame
episodes.overview: Eddie runs into his cradle-robbing first love and must decide whether to rekindle his romance with the sexy senior citizen. Then, Granny and Lucy compete to win the affections of an androgynous dispatcher and Terry discovers moisturizer.

episodes.name: Where's the Beefcake
episodes.overview: When Councilwoman Price tries to take nudity out of the annual Firefighters' Beefcake Calendar, the crew must get creative to maintain the integrity of its sexy (and oily) tradition.

episodes.name: I'm Eddie Penisi
episodes.overview: When the police captain catches Eddie sleeping with his wife days before the Tacoma FD/PD charity boxing match, he challenges Eddie to be the main event.

episodes.name: Fire at the Dispensary
episodes.overview: It's the anniversary of Terry busting a nut to save Eddie's life and the biggest football game of the year! But the party gets interrupted when a fire breaks out at a local weed dispensary - which at least ends the day on a high note!

episodes.name: Payday
episodes.overview: As Eddie prepares to become a father, the rest of the crew's wagering gets out of control, forcing Terry to ban all gambling from the firehouse. The crew finds creative ways to bet behind Chief's back, causing Lucy to fall into debt.

episodes.name: Fire in Sex Town
episodes.overview: When a perverted arsonist strikes Tacoma, the TPD and the TFD must put aside their rivalries to solve the case. To everyone's surprise, the two crews discover they are not as different as they think, but how long can the lovefest last?

episodes.name: Whodunit?
episodes.overview: Councilwoman Price tells Terry to find the author of an anonymous firefighter blog from the station and shut it down. With everyone a suspect, no one can be trusted. How quickly will they turn on each other? Who will crack? And Whodunnit?

episodes.name: Lucy Wants a Friend
episodes.overview: Longing for a female friend, Lucy convinces Chief to transfer firefighter Delilah Dunn to the station while guys on the crew try to find a macho match to their energy. Meanwhile, Eddie takes Councilwoman Price for a walk on the wild side.

episodes.name: I'm Eddie Penisi…Sr.
episodes.overview: When Fire Commissioner Eddie Penisi, Sr. shows up, Eddie and Terry seek his approval while the "commish" drives them apart. The crew plays D&D for the acceptance of their own illustrious dungeon master.

episodes.name: The C-Team
episodes.overview: Station 24 is picked to make public service announcements, forcing them to work with the buff and handsome C-Team and their new transfer Delilah. Terry buys a gas-guzzling truck and Eddie can't help but take him for a ride.

episodes.name: Fire Choir
episodes.overview: Wolf Boykins returns to lead the fire station choir, the Ex-SING-guishers. Eddie teases Granny for joining the group but soon finds himself vying for a spot as the lead whistler. Lucy, meanwhile, convinces Chief to let her look for a more female-friendly uniform.

episodes.name: The Crying Game
episodes.overview: When Lucy gets injured on the job, Eddie is tasked with heading a peer counseling session that leads the crew to learn more about themselves.

episodes.name: Ike and Mike
episodes.overview: Ike's mean twin brother Mike pays him a visit and asks for a life-changing favor. Meanwhile, the crew takes DNA tests, Granny discovers his Jewish heritage and Terry is devastated to learn that Lucy's genes are more Penisi than McConky.

episodes.name: Firefighter's Ball Part 1
episodes.overview: Terry learns some sexy new dance moves to impress Vicky at the fireman's ball. Ike volunteers to be Andy's wingman, and Lucy discovers her date is more like his mother than she realized.

episodes.name: Firefighter's Ball Part 2
episodes.overview: As the Firefighter's Ball rages on, things go off the rails. Terry and Eddie battle it out, Ike deals with Andy after too many drinks, Lucy struggles to get alone time with her date, and Granny finds a way to ease the tension with his date.

episodes.name: To Nightmare Manor
episodes.overview: It's a spooky evening for the crew when they have to answer a call at a haunted house. While they navigate the haunted halls looking for the source of the fire, each of them must confront their greatest fears.

episodes.name: A Christmas Story
episodes.overview: The holiday season has arrived at the firehouse and everyone is feeling jolly... except for Eddie. In order to get good year-end reviews, Lucy, Andy, Ike, and Granny try their hardest to get him in the Christmas spirit.

2.name: Season 2
2.overview: Season 2 finds the squad fighting fires at a haunted house, trapped in an elevator during the annual Firefighter’s Ball, and creating fire safety videos with the buffest group of firefighters in Tacoma.

episodes.name: Quarantine
episodes.overview: The gang is quarantined at the station after being exposed to a potentially infected Capuchin monkey on an emergency call. Everyone deals in their own way.

episodes.name: Hell Week
episodes.overview: Lucy graduates to official Firefighter if she can survive the gang's pranks. She insists they don't go easy just because she's Chief's daughter.

episodes.name: The Big Chill
episodes.overview: It's time for the annual firehouse chili cook-off, and everyone is excited to impress the chief, but judge Terry is affected by his wisdom teeth surgery and the drugs that go along with it.

episodes.name: How I Met Your Mother
episodes.overview: A flashback to how Terry and Vicky met and were set up by Eddie as a prank years ago. Terry, Eddie and Vicky all have very different memories of the event, but all involve Terry eating.

episodes.name: Carpet Diem
episodes.overview: The station receives a sexual harassment complaint, requiring the Crew to participate in a sexual bias seminar. Eddie falls for the teacher and tries to navigate the thorny process of how to pick up the Sexual Bias Trainer.

episodes.name: Rise of the Machines
episodes.overview: An upgrade at Station 24 brings Inferna, a new Artificial Intelligence system, intended to improve the station's efficiency and safety. While the crew enjoys the perks of a "smart" station, Eddie grows suspicious of Inferna's true agenda.

episodes.name: The Quiet Party
episodes.overview: Terry is serious about his "No Station Birthday Parties" policy, but the Crew is set on ignoring it upon finding out it's Andy's 9th Leap Year birthday. Pulling it off might be mission impossible.

episodes.name: Eddie the Chief
episodes.overview: When Terry throws out his back, Eddie becomes the interim Chief, which creates tension over whose methods are best.

episodes.name: Wedding Crashers
episodes.overview: When Lucy's secret date with a Tacoma police officer ends in embarrassment, the firefighters and the local police struggle to manage the aftermath.

episodes.name: Eddie's Exes
episodes.overview: Eddie learns his divorce lawyer was never really a lawyer and that his multiple divorces were never really finalized. The crew chips in for the latest Pedalton bike for the station but all fall for the same trainer.

episodes.name: Thanksgiving
episodes.overview: It's Thanksgiving Day in the station, and as usual, Terry wants to do everything his way, but no one gets their way once an engine breaks down. Spatchcock, an irritating mechanic, is summoned at the TFD.

episodes.name: Pickleball
episodes.overview: The annual TFD Pickleball Tournament is underway and Terry & Eddie's team are long-running-and-very-cocky station champs, but the crew has plans to finally take them and their attitudes down.

episodes.name: Fire at the Fire Station
episodes.overview: The Firefighters are out on a call when a fire breaks out at home Station 24.

episodes.name: Pirate World FD
episodes.overview: The crew hopes to return to their burnt-down station but must convince a reluctant Eddie to join them… And exorcise a few demons in the process.

episodes.name: The Probie Imbroglio
episodes.overview: The Crew welcomes Mickleberry, a new probie, to the shift, but they quickly realize a funny name is not a good reason for picking a new Firefighter.

episodes.name: The Penisi Way
episodes.overview: When a mysterious old trunk is found hidden in a wall at Station 24, Eddie discovers that its contents hold secrets that were better left buried.

episodes.name: Who Gives A-Shift?
episodes.overview: When two shifts are forced to share duties at Station 24, the challenge is on to determine which shift is the Chief’s favorite.

episodes.name: Death Photo
episodes.overview: As the firefighters prepare for their annual station photos, otherwise known as the “Death Photo,” each crew member goes to extravagant lengths to make sure theirs is a good one.

episodes.name: Valentine's Day
episodes.overview: It’s Valentine’s Day in the station. As Eddie juggles his various romances, Terry and Vicky set out to teach Lucy a valuable lesson about love.

episodes.name: Big Trouble in Little Belgium
episodes.overview: Ike’s dark past comes back to haunt him when the Crew learns he used to run with a gang on the tough streets of Tacoma’s Little Belgium.

episodes.name: Chicken Fight
episodes.overview: Amidst some fun in the sun at Terry’s annual Summer Pool Party, the Crew tries to work up the courage to tell the Chief his Famous BBQ Chicken just isn’t that great.

episodes.name: Gone Dutch
episodes.overview: The Crew participates in a time-honored tradition, the Firefighter Wake, where they encounter plenty of tears, booze, laughs and fistfights.

episodes.name: Firefighters Only
episodes.overview: Ike invests in a Firefighters’ Only dating site, but when the rest of the Crew signs up, each has their own unique trouble finding love.

episodes.name: It's a Penisi-ful Life
episodes.overview: When Eddie questions whether his Crew appreciates him, he’s given a glimpse of what life would be like without him, only to find the vision not so comforting.

episodes.name: Kangaroo Court
episodes.overview: A fun firefighter tradition of holding a mock trial for station offenses turns “not so fun” when some eye-opening accusations are brought against Chief McConky.

episodes.name: Bad Blood
episodes.overview: The Annual Fire Department Blood Drive goes from good to bad when the Firefighters are forced to team up for charity with the Local Cops.

4.name: Season 4
4.overview: With Eddie employed by Shondaland and Andy leaving for the carpeting business, there are some big changes in the newly rebuilt (and slightly off-kilter) Station 24. A new Andy joins the crew, a wide-eyed probie who becomes the target of some comic hazing.
